<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key Eb (3 flats). LH uses open Eb: Eb2-Bb2-Eb3-G3; Cm: C2-G2-C3-Eb3; Bb: Bb2-F3-Bb3-Db4.
- RH stays light: 2-note thirds above melody range, avoiding melody doubling.
- Bar 9-10 (middle section): Cm7 anticipation; fuller LH voicing building to climax.
- Bar 11 (Cm/Bbm): LH switches between Cm and Bbm for color.
- Bars 13-14: F and Fm provide modal color before final Eb cadence.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH ascending line bars 3,7 (Bb→C→Db→Eb) mirrors melody motion.
- LH bass descends Eb-Bb-F stepwise in bars 3-4 (contrary to ascending melody).
- Common tone Eb/G shared between Eb and Cm chords, held in LH.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup + bars 1-4: moderate, establishing Eb tonic
- Bars 5-8: exact repeat with richer RH figuration
- Bars 9-11: climax with Cm7 and extended Eb
- Bars 12-14: resolution, final Eb close
-->
